Two of my favorite musicians of all time.  I still miss Harrison.  I always identified with him more than the other Beatles.  (As much as a minimally-talented kid in the early 60s could identify with the Lords of all the Realm, as they were.)

@Vaer

As I was typing the answer the song was running through my mind and I knew someone would post it here.  Or if, not, I'd do the honors.

Many have written and performed songs about being on the road as a travelling musician (Jackson Browne, Bob Seger, et. al.) but this one is the simplest, most honest and most beautiful.  And here, the one-man-band Simon sits next to a man known mostly for his role in the most famous four-man-band ever, but handles the stool-sitting, acoustic gig with ease and style.  Great video.

